The man tried to flee when police officers approached his vehicle on Thursday, but he was apprehended shortly thereafter. CAPE TOWN - A 30-year-old man from Strandfontein will appear in the Wynberg Magistrates Court soon for the possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition.He tried to flee when police officers approached his vehicle on Thursday, but he was apprehended shortly thereafter.The police s Frederick Van Wyk said: Upon approaching the vehicle, the driver tried to flee and was apprehended and upon searching the vehicle, a .38 chrome special Rossi revolver with 5 .38 rounds inside a leather holster was found under the driver s seat in the vehicle. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)